descp2: Interpolation method used to resample the image if the     target size is different from that of the loaded image.     Supported methods are "nearest", "bilinear", and "bicubic".     If PIL version 1.1.3 or newer is installed, "lanczos" is also     supported. If PIL version 3.4.0 or newer is installed, "box" and     "hamming" are also supported. By default, "nearest" is used.`
